<TITLE>EEE Split Lines</TITLE>

</HEAD><BODY ><H1>EEE Split Lines</H1>

This script reflects back the contents of a text file after
wrapping lines at a user-specified length.

<STRONG>This feature only works with Netscape 2.0 browsers.</STRONG>

<P>
Select the <VAR>browse</VAR> button to choose a text file
to upload.  When you press the submit button, this script
will process and reflect the contents of the file.

<FORM METHOD="POST"  
ACTION="http://eee.oac.uci.edu/tools/filter/splitlines"
ENCTYPE=multipart/form-data>

Enter the file to process:<INPUT TYPE="file" NAME="filename"><BR>

<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="content" Value="text" CHECKED>Reflect as plaintext 
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="content" Value="html">Reflect as hypertext<br>

Enter the maximum number of characters that can appear on a
line:<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="MAX" VALUE="" SIZE=3> (Default = 72)<br>

<INPUT TYPE="submit" NAME="submit" VALUE="Process File">
<INPUT TYPE="reset">
</FORM>

